<div class="story">
<p>Palmer's Island is a small upscale community at the very northernmost reach of Duck where the land is the narrowest. There are 15 lots which are spread out so that there is only one lot from the sound to the ocean offering each property open water views of the sound and ocean. Palmer's Island enjoys the same amenities as <a href="https://www.outerbankshome.com/outer banks/real estate/duck/sanderling.asp" title="Sanderling">Sanderling</a> and they have an active home owners association and an HOA fee. You will find Palmer's Island at the very end of Dare County, just before you get to  <a href="https://www.outerbankshome.com/outer banks/real estate/corolla/pine-island.asp" title="Pine Island">Pine Island</a> in <a href="https://www.outerbankshome.com/outer banks/real estate/corolla/" title="Corolla">Corolla</a>.</p>
